<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910813-0070</DOCNO><DOCID>910813-0070.</DOCID><HL>   Financing Business:   NL Industries Inc.</HL><DATE>08/13/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C18</SO><CO>   NL</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)</IN><NS>BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, REPURCHASES, SWAPS (BBK)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   NL INDUSTRIES Inc. said it began a previously announcedoffer to buy as many as 10 million of its shares in a &quot;Dutchauction&quot; tender offer. The Houston chemical concern,controlled by Dallas investor Harold Simmons, has said itwill offer to buy its shares at between $14.50 and $17.50 ashare. Under a Dutch auction tender offer, shareholders maytender their shares at any price within that range. Thecompany will pay the lowest price it can to buy the 10million shares. NL Industries said the offer will expireSept. 11 at 5 p.m. EDT unless it is extended by the company.NL Industries has about 63.4 million shares outstanding.Salomon Brothers Inc. is managing the offer.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>